trans-unit.source: Provides a managed representation of a Win32 `OVERLAPPED` structure, including methods to transfer information from an Overlapped instance to a <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"></xref> structure.
trans-unit.target: Inneholder en behandlet representasjon av en Win32 `OVERLAPPED` strukturen, inkludert metoder for å overføre informasjon fra en overlappet forekomst til en <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"> </xref> struktur.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%2A> and <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A> methods transfer information from an Overlapped object to a <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> structure that can be passed to Win32 API functions for asynchronous file I/O.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%2A>og <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A>metoder overføring av informasjon fra et overlappet-objekt til en <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>-strukturen som kan sendes til Win32 API-funksjoner for asynkrone filen i/u.</xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> </xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A> </xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%2A>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> method transfers information from a <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> structure to an instance of the Overlapped class.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A>Informasjon om overføring fra en <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>struktur til en forekomst av klassen overlappet.</xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> </xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A>

trans-unit.source: Changes to the properties of an Overlapped object affect its associated <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> structure, and vice versa.
trans-unit.target: Endringer i Egenskaper for et objekt som overlappet innvirkning på de tilknyttede <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>strukturen og omvendt.</xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new, empty instance of the <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny, tom forekomst av den <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"></xref> class with the specified file position, the 32-bit integer handle to an event that is signaled when the I/O operation is complete, and an interface through which to return the results of the operation.

trans-unit.source: Frees the unmanaged memory associated with a native overlapped structure allocated by the <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack*> method.
trans-unit.target: Frigjør uforvaltede minnet som er knyttet til en opprinnelig overlappende struktur som er tildelt av den <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack*>metoden.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack*>

trans-unit.source: You must call the Free method exactly once on every <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> pointer you receive from the <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Du må kalle metoden gratis nøyaktig én gang på hver <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>pekeren du mottar fra den <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%2A> </xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>

trans-unit.source: If you don't call the Free method, you will leak memory.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du ikke kalle metoden gratis, vil du ut minne.

trans-unit.source: If you call the Free method more than once, memory will be corrupted.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du kaller metoden gratis mer enn én gang, bli minnet skadet.

trans-unit.source: Packs the current instance into a <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"></xref> structure, specifying the delegate to be invoked when the asynchronous I/O operation is complete.
trans-unit.target: Administrasjonspakkene den gjeldende forekomsten til en <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"> </xref> strukturen som angir representanten som skal aktiveres når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: The unmanaged pointer returned by this method can be passed to the operating system in overlapped I/O operations.
trans-unit.target: Ubehandlet pekeren returneres av denne metoden kan sendes til operativsystemet i overlappende i/u-operasjoner.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> structure is fixed in physical memory until <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>strukturen er fast i minnet før <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> </xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>

trans-unit.source: > [!IMPORTANT] > The caller is responsible for pinning the buffer.
trans-unit.target: > [!IMPORTANT] > Oppkalleren er ansvarlig for å feste bufferen.

trans-unit.source: If the application domain is unloaded, however, the handle to the pinned buffer is destroyed and the buffer is released, leaving the I/O operation to write to the freed address.
trans-unit.target: Hvis programdomenet er fjernet, men håndtaket for festet bufferen er ødelagt bufferen som er utgitt, slik at i/u-operasjon for å skrive til frigjort adressen

trans-unit.source: For this reason, it is better to use the <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%28System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback%2CSystem.Object%29> method overload, in which the runtime pins the buffer.
trans-unit.target: Derfor er det best å bruke den <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%28System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback%2CSystem.Object%29>metoden overbelastning, der kjøretiden PIN-bufferen.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Pack%28System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback%2CSystem.Object%29>

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"></xref> delegate that represents the callback method invoked when the asynchronous I/O operation completes.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"> </xref> representanten som representerer metoden tilbakeringing aktiveres når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: Packs the current instance into a <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"></xref> structure, specifying a delegate that is invoked when the asynchronous I/O operation is complete and a managed object that serves as a buffer.
trans-unit.target: Administrasjonspakkene den gjeldende forekomsten til en <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"> </xref> strukturen som angir en representant som aktiveres når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført, og en behandlede objektet som fungerer som en buffer.

trans-unit.source: The unmanaged pointer returned by this method can be passed to the operating system in overlapped I/O operations.
trans-unit.target: Ubehandlet pekeren returneres av denne metoden kan sendes til operativsystemet i overlappende i/u-operasjoner.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> structure is fixed in physical memory until <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>strukturen er fast i minnet før <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> </xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>

trans-unit.source: The buffer or buffers specified in `userData` must be the same as those passed to the unmanaged operating system function that performs the asynchronous I/O.
trans-unit.target: Bufferlengden eller buffere som er angitt i `userData` må være de samme som sendes til funksjonen uforvaltede operativsystemet som utfører asynkront i/u.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The runtime pins the buffer or buffers specified in `userData` for the duration of the I/O operation.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Kjøretiden PIN-bufferen eller buffere som er angitt i `userData` i løpet av i/u-operasjon.

trans-unit.source: If the application domain is unloaded, the runtime keeps the memory pinned until the I/O operation completes.
trans-unit.target: Hvis programdomenet er fjernet, beholder kjøretiden minne festet til i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"></xref> delegate that represents the callback method invoked when the asynchronous I/O operation completes.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"> </xref> representanten som representerer metoden tilbakeringing aktiveres når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: An object or array of objects representing the input or output buffer for the operation.
trans-unit.target: Et objekt eller en matrise av objekter som representerer inndata eller utdata bufferen for operasjonen.

trans-unit.source: Each object represents a buffer, for example an array of bytes.
trans-unit.target: Hvert objekt som representerer en buffer, for eksempel en bytematrise.

trans-unit.source: > [!CAUTION] > Using the <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A> method could inadvertently open up a security hole.

trans-unit.source: Code access security bases its permission checks on the permissions of all the callers on the stack.
trans-unit.target: Kodetilgangssikkerhet baseres tillatelse kontrollen i tillatelsene for alle brukere på stakken.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A> method does not propagate the calling stack.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A>metoden ikke overføre kall stakken.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.UnsafePack%2A>

trans-unit.source: Malicious code might be able to exploit this to avoid permission checks.
trans-unit.target: Skadelig kode kanskje utnytte dette for å unngå tillatelse database.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"></xref> delegate that represents the callback method invoked when the asynchronous I/O operation completes.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"> </xref> representanten som representerer metoden tilbakeringing aktiveres når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: An unmanaged pointer to a <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"></xref> structure.
trans-unit.target: En ubehandlet peker til en <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"> </xref> struktur.

trans-unit.source: The current <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"></xref> has already been packed.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"> </xref> er allerede pakket.

trans-unit.source: Packs the current instance into a <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"></xref> structure, specifying the delegate to invoke when the asynchronous I/O operation is complete and the managed object that serves as a buffer.
trans-unit.target: Administrasjonspakkene den gjeldende forekomsten til en <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"> </xref> strukturen angir representanten å aktivere når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført, og den forvaltede objekt som fungerer som en buffer.

trans-unit.source: Does not propagate the calling stack.
trans-unit.target: Ikke overføre kall stakken.

trans-unit.source: The unmanaged pointer returned by this method can be passed to the operating system in overlapped I/O operations.
trans-unit.target: Ubehandlet pekeren returneres av denne metoden kan sendes til operativsystemet i overlappende i/u-operasjoner.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped> structure is fixed in physical memory until <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>strukturen er fast i minnet før <xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Threading.Overlapped.Unpack%2A> </xref:System.Threading.NativeOverlapped>

trans-unit.source: The buffer or buffers specified in `userData` must be the same as those passed to the unmanaged operating system function that performs the asynchronous I/O.
trans-unit.target: Bufferlengden eller buffere som er angitt i `userData` må være de samme som sendes til funksjonen uforvaltede operativsystemet som utfører asynkront i/u.

trans-unit.source: The runtime pins the buffer or buffers specified in`userData` for the duration of the I/O operation.
trans-unit.target: Kjøretiden PIN-bufferen eller buffere som er angitt i`userData` i løpet av i/u-operasjon.

trans-unit.source: If the application domain is unloaded, the runtime keeps the memory pinned until the I/O operation completes.
trans-unit.target: Hvis programdomenet er fjernet, beholder kjøretiden minne festet til i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: > [!CAUTION] > Using the UnsafePack method could inadvertently open up a security hole.
trans-unit.target: > [!CAUTION] > Ved hjelp av UnsafePack metoden kan utilsiktet åpner et hull i sikkerheten.

trans-unit.source: Code access security bases its permission checks on the permissions of all the callers on the stack.
trans-unit.target: Kodetilgangssikkerhet baseres tillatelse kontrollen i tillatelsene for alle brukere på stakken.

trans-unit.source: The UnsafePack method does not propagate the calling stack.
trans-unit.target: Metoden UnsafePack overføre ikke kall stakken.

trans-unit.source: Malicious code might be able to exploit this to avoid permission checks.
trans-unit.target: Skadelig kode kanskje utnytte dette for å unngå tillatelse database.

trans-unit.source: An <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"></xref> delegate that represents the callback method invoked when the asynchronous I/O operation completes.
trans-unit.target: En <xref href="System.Threading.IOCompletionCallback"> </xref> representanten som representerer metoden tilbakeringing aktiveres når den asynkrone i/u-operasjonen er fullført.

trans-unit.source: An object or array of objects representing the input or output buffer for the operation.
trans-unit.target: Et objekt eller en matrise av objekter som representerer inndata eller utdata bufferen for operasjonen.

trans-unit.source: Each object represents a buffer, for example an array of bytes.
trans-unit.target: Hvert objekt som representerer en buffer, for eksempel en bytematrise.

trans-unit.source: An unmanaged pointer to a <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"></xref> structure.
trans-unit.target: En ubehandlet peker til en <xref href="System.Threading.NativeOverlapped"> </xref> struktur.

trans-unit.source: The caller does not have the required permission.
trans-unit.target: Oppkalleren har ikke den nødvendige tillatelsen.

trans-unit.source: The current <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"></xref> is already packed.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende <xref href="System.Threading.Overlapped"> </xref> er allerede pakket.
